radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled, measuring 13 mm, with wall thickening and periappendiceal fat stranding. A 4 x 5 mm fecalith is noted at the cecal base. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenals, kidneys, stomach, small bowel loops, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, distal ureters, and soft tissues are all within normal limits. There is a small amount of simple free fluid in the pelvis. No intra-abdominal free air or abscess.
